Police Command in Katsina state, has dismissed the rumours making the round of an alleged kidnap of forty persons along Jibia to Batsari road in the state. In a press statement signed by SP Gambo Isah, the State Police Public Relation Officer (PPRO) and made available to journalists on Tuesday, explained that what actually occurred along the area wasn’t objectively reported. According to the statement, “What truly happened was that yesterday (5/01/2020) at about 18:00hrs, bandits numbering over sixty, armed with AK 47 rifles blocked Jibia – Batsari road, exactly at Ruma village and forcefully stopped two J5 motor vehicles and took the occupants of the vehicles into the bush”. “The search party led by Operation Puff Adder went after the hoodlums but succeeded in rescuing all the victims with the exception of seven others.” The statement added that the command in collaboration with community members are combing the bush, with a view to rescuing the remaining seven persons undiscovered. He listed their names as Maazu Yasore, Alhaji Nuhu, Kabiru Hashimu, Dan Asibi Tela, Sani Kokari, Nura Shambal and Ali Dan Maituwo. Meanwhile, residents of the place are still holding claims of the missing 38 to 40 persons who might be in the kidnapper’s custody.